{
  "id": "019cf612-df07-7940-91ab-e83ac89d7e6f",
  "content": "# M3.4: Graph Edge Improvements — Design\n\n> **Status:** Shipped (v0.3.0)\n\n**Goal:** Fix the graph edge creation pipeline so that graph-expanded retrieval produces meaningfully different results from vector-only retrieval.\n\n**Problem Statement:** The current ingestion pipeline creates 236 edges for 2,207 chunks, and nearly all edges are intra-file (same-file `contains`, `implements`, self-referential `imports`). Graph expansion during search finds 0-2 additional results per query — indistinguishable from vector-only. Three root causes were identified through benchmark investigation.\n\n**Milestone:** M3.4 (follows M3.3 embedding/chunking pipeline)\n\n---\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-04-m3.4-graph-edge-improvements-design.md",
